<seg id="1">LeBron to make Lakers debut Sunday in San Diego</seg>
<seg id="2">The wait is nearly over for fans looking to see LeBron James make his first start for the Los Angeles Lakers.</seg>
<seg id="3">Lakers coach Luke Walton has announced that James will play in Sunday's preseason opener against the Denver Nuggets in San Diego.</seg>
<seg id="4">But just how many minutes he'll play has yet to be determined.</seg>
<seg id="5">"It will be more than one and less than 48," said Walton on the Lakers" official website.</seg>
<seg id="6">Lakers reporter Mike Trudell tweeted that James will likely play limited minutes.</seg>
<seg id="7">Following practice earlier this week, James was asked about his plans for the Lakers" six-game preseason schedule.</seg>
<seg id="8">"I don't need preseason games at this stage of my career to get ready," he said.</seg>
</p>
